      <div class="card mb-4">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title">1. Add Skills to Practice</h5>
          <p class="card-text">
            Start by adding skills you want to master. Group them by subjects to stay organized.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card mb-4">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title">2. Follow Your Schedule</h5>
          <p class="card-text">
            Check your One Day Agenda or Calendar to see what to practice each day. 
            Our spaced repetition system schedules reviews at increasing intervals: today, tomorrow, 2 days later, 4 days later, and so on.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card mb-4">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title">3. Rate Your Practice</h5>
          <p class="card-text">
            After practicing, rate how well you did from 1-5 stars. Your ratings help track progress and adjust future practice intervals.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title">4. Track Your Progress</h5>
          <p class="card-text">
            Watch your skills improve as you consistently practice at the right intervals. The spaced repetition system helps you learn efficiently and remember for the long term.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
